        jTextArea1.setText("Description of product:\n- This software, Student Portfolio Generator, will generate individual student portfolios using data from an excel file provided by user.\n\nUse:\n- In this window please input n all the fields:\n1. Excel file location address can be found in the view finder, copy and paste the address\n2. Excel file name must be identical, including extension. For example: SampelGradebook.xlsx\n3. Excel spreadsheet name must be identical with what is enetered in your file\n4. Please tick only 1 check box, if checked the wrong checkbox, please uncheck and then check the correct check box\n\nIf your are receiving errors, please check your inputs, otherwise, please check if your excel document is correctly formated.\nKeywords:\n-\t‘Trimester 1’, ‘Trimester 2’, ‘Trimester 3’\n-\tTest \n-\tFinal\nNote: Without quotation marks, meaning that it can be written in any form, for instance:\n-\tTest, TEST, test, TEst, TeST….\n\nImportant format:\n-\tThe name column must be in the same row as ‘Trimester X’\n-\tTitles must be placed right below the row where ‘Trimester X’ is\n-\tAll titles must be in line\n-\tNumber of students is best to be consistent in trimesters\n\t\tAdd student names with no grades if needed\n-\tFor now, the program only recognizes the cell style of percentage\n-\tFor now, the program only recognizes the cell type of numbers and string\n-\tBest effect to not use merge cells, but it will not bug the program\n-\tDo not have blank row between students\n\n\n");
